The paper discusses unsupervised learning using autoencoders, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The focus on denoising and regularisation suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The use of autoencoders for classification and sample synthesis suggests that the paper may also belong to "cs.CV" (Computer Vision) and "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence). The use of adversarial training suggests that the paper may belong to "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of denoising suggests that the paper may also belong to "cs.CL" (Computation and Language).
